question: List the id, first name and last name of the customers who both have placed more than 2 orders and have bought at least 3 items.

answer: SELECT T1.customer_id , T1.customer_first_name , T1.customer_last_name FROM Customers AS T1 JOIN Orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING COUNT(T2.order_id) > 2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_id , T1.customer_first_name , T1.customer_last_name FROM Customers AS T1 JOIN Order_items AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.order_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING COUNT(T2.order_item_id) >= 3

question: List the biographical data and student id for the students who take 2 or more classes and the students who have less than 2 detentions.
solution: SELECT T1.bio_data ,  T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 UNION SELECT T1.bio_data ,  T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Detention AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  <  2
answer: SELECT T1.bio_data , T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 INNER JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING COUNT(T2.class_id) >= 2 UNION SELECT T1.bio_data , T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 INNER JOIN Detention AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING COUNT(T2.detention_id) < 2

answer: SELECT T1.bio_data , T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 INNER JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING COUNT(T2.class_id) >= 2 UNION SELECT T1.bio_data , T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 INNER JOIN Detention AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING COUNT(T2.detention_id) < 2

question: List the details of the teachers who teach some class whose detail has the substring 'data' but do not teach a class whose detail contains the prefix 'net'
solution: SELECT T1.teacher_details FROM Teachers AS T1 JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id  =  T2.teacher_id WHERE T2.class_details LIKE '%data%' EXCEPT SELECT T1.teacher_details FROM Teachers AS T1 JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id  =  T2.teacher_id WHERE T2.class_details LIKE 'net%'
answer: SELECT T1.teacher_details FROM Teachers AS T1 INNER JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id = T2.teacher_id WHERE T2.class_details LIKE '%data%' EXCEPT SELECT T1.teacher_details FROM Teachers AS T1 INNER JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id = T2.teacher_id WHERE T2.class_details LIKE 'net%'

answer: SELECT T1.teacher_details FROM Teachers AS T1 INNER JOIN Classes AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id = T2.teacher_id WHERE T2.class_details LIKE '%data%' AND T2.class_details NOT LIKE 'net%'

question: Which students not only got the most common result but also got a result obtained by 3 students in behaviour monitoring? List the student's biographical data and details.
solution: SELECT T1.bio_data ,  T1.student_details FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Behaviour_Monitoring AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id WHERE T2.behaviour_monitoring_details IN ( SELECT behaviour_monitoring_details FROM Behaviour_Monitoring GROUP BY behaviour_monitoring_details ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1 ) INTERSECT SELECT T1.bio_data ,  T1.student_details FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Behaviour_Monitoring AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id WHERE T2.behaviour_monitoring_details IN ( SELECT behaviour_monitoring_details FROM Behaviour_Monitoring GROUP BY behaviour_monitoring_details HAVING count(*)  =  3 )
answer: SELECT T1.bio_data, T1.student_details FROM Students AS T1 INNER JOIN Behaviour_Monitoring AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T2.behaviour_monitoring_details HAVING COUNT(T2.student_id) = 3

answer: SELECT T1.document_subset_id, T1.document_subset_name, count(T2.document_object_id) FROM Document_Subsets AS T1 INNER JOIN Document_Subset_Members AS T2 ON T1.document_subset_id = T2.document_subset_id GROUP BY T1.document_subset_id ORDER BY count(T2.document_object_id) DESC LIMIT 1

question: For the document subset with the most number of different documents , what are the ids and names of the subset , as well as the number of documents ?

answer: SELECT T1.document_subset_id, T1.document_subset_name, count(T2.document_object_id) FROM Document_Subsets AS T1 INNER JOIN Document_Subset_Members AS T2 ON T1.document_subset_id = T2.document_subset_id GROUP BY T1.document_subset_id ORDER BY count(T2.document_object_id) DESC LIMIT 1

question: List all document subsets of documents that related to each document id. List the name of document subset and the document id.
solution: SELECT DISTINCT T3.Document_Subset_Name ,  T1.Document_Object_ID FROM Document_Subset_Members AS T1 JOIN Document_Subset_Members  AS T2 ON T1.Related_Document_Object_ID = T2.Document_Object_ID JOIN Document_Subsets AS T3 ON T2.Document_Subset_ID =  T3.Document_Subset_ID
answer: SELECT T1.document_subset_name, T2.document_object_id FROM Document_Subsets AS T1 INNER JOIN Document_Subset_Members AS T2 ON T1.document_subset_id = T2.document_subset_id

question: What are the different subsets of documents related to each document id , list the name of the document subset and id of the actual document ?
solution: select distinct t3.document_subset_name ,  t1.document_object_id from document_subset_members as t1 join document_subset_members  as t2 on t1.related_document_object_id = t2.document_object_id join document_subsets as t3 on t2.document_subset_id =  t3.document_subset_id
answer: SELECT T3.document_subset_name, T2.document_object_id FROM Document_Subset_Members AS T1 INNER JOIN Document_Objects AS T2 ON T1.document_object_id = T2.document_object_id INNER JOIN Document_Subsets AS T3 ON T1.document_subset_id = T3.document_subset_id

question: List the Collection Name that document owned by 'Ransom ' belong to .
solution: select t1.collection_name from collections as t1 join documents_in_collections as t2 on t1.collection_id = t2.collection_id join document_objects as t3 on t2.document_object_id  =  t3.document_object_id where t3.owner  =  'ransom'
answer: SELECT T1.Collection_Name FROM Collections AS T1 INNER JOIN Documents_in_Collections AS T2 ON T1.Collection_ID = T2.Collection_ID INNER JOIN Document_Objects AS T3 ON T2.Document_Object_ID = T3.Document_Object_ID WHERE T3.Owner = 'Ransom'

solution: SELECT t1.name ,  sum(t2.quantity) FROM store AS t1 JOIN stock AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id GROUP BY t2.store_id ORDER BY sum(t2.quantity) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T3.Name , T2.Quantity FROM stock AS T2 INNER JOIN store AS T3 ON T2.Store_ID = T3.Store_ID GROUP BY T2.Store_ID ORDER BY SUM(T2.Quantity) DESC LIMIT 1

question: Which store has the headphones in stock? Give me the store name and the total quantity.

question: How many papers are published in year 2009 by Columbia University?
solution: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.paper_id) FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Affiliation AS T3 ON T2.affiliation_id  =  T3.affiliation_id WHERE T3.name LIKE "Columbia University" AND T1.year  =  2009

question: What are the titles and paper ids for papers that have Mckeown, Kathleen or Rambow, Owen in their author list?
solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.title ,  T1.paper_id FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Author AS T3 ON T2.author_id  =  T3.author_id WHERE  T3.name LIKE "%Mckeown ,  Kathleen%" OR T3.name LIKE "%Rambow ,  Owen%"
answer: SELECT T1.title , T1.paper_id FROM Paper AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.paper_id INNER JOIN Author AS T3 ON T2.author_id = T3.author_id WHERE (T3.name = 'Mckeown, Kathleen' OR T3.name = 'Rambow, Owen')

question: List the names of all authors and their number of papers in descending order by number of papers.
solution: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC
answer: SELECT T1.name , COUNT(T2.paper_id) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY COUNT(T2.paper_id) DESC

question: How many papers did each author publish, ordered by number of papers?
solution: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC
answer: SELECT T1.name , count(T2.paper_id) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY count(T2.paper_id) DESC

question: List all affiliations with ascending ordered number of papers.
solution: SELECT T1.name FROM Affiliation AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id  =  T2.affiliation_id GROUP BY T1.affiliation_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Affiliation AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id = T2.affiliation_id GROUP BY T1.affiliation_id ORDER BY COUNT(T2.paper_id) ASC

question: List names of all authors who have more than 50 papers.
solution: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id HAVING count(*)  >  50
answer: SELECT t1.name FROM author AS t1 JOIN author_list AS t2 ON t1.author_id = t2.author_id GROUP BY t2.author_id HAVING count(*) > 50

question: What are the names of all authors who have more than 50 papers?
solution: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id HAVING count(*)  >  50
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.name HAVING COUNT(T2.paper_id) > 50

question: List names of all authors who have only 1 paper.
solution: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id HAVING count(*)  =  1
answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id GROUP BY T2.author_id HAVING COUNT(T2.paper_id) = 1

question: What are the names of authors who have exactly 1 paper?
solution: SELECT T1.name FROM Author AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T1.author_id HAVING count(*)  =  1
answer: SELECT t1.name FROM author AS t1 JOIN author_list AS t2 ON t1.author_id = t2.author_id GROUP BY t2.author_id HAVING count(*) = 1

question: What is the venue and year with the most number of publications?
solution: SELECT venue ,  YEAR FROM paper GROUP BY venue ,  YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT venue , YEAR FROM Paper GROUP BY venue , YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What is the venue with the least number of publications?
solution: SELECT venue FROM paper GROUP BY venue ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT venue FROM paper GROUP BY venue ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT venue FROM Paper GROUP BY venue ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

question: What is the id and the number of citations of the most cited paper?
solution: SELECT paper_id ,  count(*) FROM Citation GROUP BY cited_paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.paper_id , count(*) FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Citation AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.cited_paper_id GROUP BY T1.paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: Give the id and the number of citations of the most cited paper.
solution: SELECT paper_id ,  count(*) FROM Citation GROUP BY cited_paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.paper_id , count(*) FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Citation AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.cited_paper_id GROUP BY T1.paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: Give the title of the paper which cites most number of papers?

question: What is the title of the paper which cites the most other papers?

question: List top 10 most cited papers and their numbers of citations.
solution: SELECT paper_id ,  count(*) FROM Citation GROUP BY cited_paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 10
answer: SELECT T1.paper_id , count(*) AS num FROM Paper AS T1 INNER JOIN Citation AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.cited_paper_id GROUP BY T1.paper_id ORDER BY num DESC LIMIT 10

question: What are the 10 most cited papers, and how many citations did each have?
solution: SELECT paper_id ,  count(*) FROM Citation GROUP BY cited_paper_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 10
answer: SELECT T1.paper_id , COUNT(T2.cited_paper_id) FROM Paper AS T1 LEFT JOIN Citation AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.cited_paper_id GROUP BY T1.paper_id ORDER BY COUNT(T2.cited_paper_id) DESC LIMIT 10

question: How many citations does Mckeown , Kathleen have ?
solution: select count(*) from citation as t1 join author_list as t2 on t1.cited_paper_id  =  t2.paper_id join author as t3 on t2.author_id  =  t3.author_id where t3.name = "mckeown ,  kathleen"
answer: SELECT COUNT(T1.cited_paper_id) FROM Citation AS T1 INNER JOIN Paper AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.paper_id INNER JOIN Author_list AS T3 ON T2.paper_id = T3.paper_id INNER JOIN Author AS T4 ON T3.author_id = T4.author_id WHERE T4.name = 'Mckeown , Kathleen'

question: Count the number of citations Mckeown , Kathleen has .

answer: SELECT count(*) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id INNER JOIN Paper AS T3 ON T2.paper_id = T3.paper_id INNER JOIN Citation AS T4 ON T3.paper_id = T4.paper_id WHERE T1.name = 'Mckeown , Kathleen'

question: Find the name and number of citations of the author who has most citations among all authors?
solution: SELECT T3.name ,  count(*) FROM Citation AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.cited_paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Author AS T3 ON T2.author_id  =  T3.author_id GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.name , COUNT(*) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What is the name and number of citations of the author with the greatest number of citations among authors?
solution: SELECT T3.name ,  count(*) FROM Citation AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.cited_paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Author AS T3 ON T2.author_id  =  T3.author_id GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.name , COUNT(T2.cited_paper_id) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Citation AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.paper_id GROUP BY T1.author_id ORDER BY COUNT(T2.cited_paper_id) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What are the venues and years where Mckeown , Kathleen had papers ?
solution: select distinct t1.venue ,  t1.year from paper as t1 join author_list as t2 on t1.paper_id  =  t2.paper_id join author as t3 on t2.author_id  =  t3.author_id where t3.name = "mckeown ,  kathleen"
answer: SELECT T1.venue , T1.year FROM Paper AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.paper_id INNER JOIN Author AS T3 ON T2.author_id = T3.author_id WHERE T3.name = 'Mckeown , Kathleen'

question: Which author had the most papers in the year 2009?
solution: SELECT T3.name FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Author AS T3 ON T3.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T1.year  =  2009 GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT t1.name FROM author AS t1 INNER JOIN author_list AS t2 ON t1.author_id = t2.author_id INNER JOIN paper AS t3 ON t2.paper_id = t3.paper_id WHERE t3.year = 2009 GROUP BY t1.name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What is the name of the author with the most papers in 2009?
solution: SELECT T3.name FROM Paper AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id  =  T2.paper_id JOIN Author AS T3 ON T3.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T1.year  =  2009 GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT t1.name FROM author AS t1 INNER JOIN author_list AS t2 ON t1.author_id = t2.author_id INNER JOIN paper AS t3 ON t2.paper_id = t3.paper_id WHERE t3.year = 2009 GROUP BY t1.name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What are the names of the top 3 affiliations that have the most papers in year 2009?

answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Affiliation AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id = T2.affiliation_id INNER JOIN Paper AS T3 ON T2.paper_id = T3.paper_id WHERE T3.year = 2009 GROUP BY T1.affiliation_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 affiliations had the most papers in 2009?

answer: SELECT T1.name FROM Affiliation AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id = T2.affiliation_id INNER JOIN Paper AS T3 ON T2.paper_id = T3.paper_id WHERE T3.year = 2009 GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY COUNT(T2.paper_id) DESC LIMIT 3

question: How many papers does Columbia University have in or before 2009 ?

answer: SELECT count(*) FROM Paper AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.paper_id = T2.paper_id INNER JOIN Affiliation AS T3 ON T3.affiliation_id = T2.affiliation_id WHERE T3.name = 'Columbia University' AND T1.year <= 2009

question: Find the total number of papers for each affiliation.
solution: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.paper_id) ,  T1.name FROM Affiliation AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id  =  T2.affiliation_id GROUP BY T1.affiliation_id
answer: SELECT T1.name , count(T2.paper_id) FROM Affiliation AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.affiliation_id = T2.affiliation_id GROUP BY T1.affiliation_id

question: Find the titles of papers that have more than 50 citations.
solution: SELECT T2.title FROM Citation AS T1 JOIN Paper AS T2 ON T1.cited_paper_id  =  T2.paper_id GROUP BY T1.cited_paper_id HAVING count(*)  >  50
answer: SELECT t1.title FROM paper AS t1 JOIN citation AS t2 ON t1.paper_id = t2.cited_paper_id GROUP BY t2.cited_paper_id HAVING count(*) > 50

question: Find the number of authors who did not publish any paper that is cited more than 50 times.
solution: SELECT count(*) FROM Author WHERE Author_id NOT IN ( SELECT T2.author_id FROM Citation AS T1 JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.cited_paper_id  =  T2.paper_id GROUP BY T1.cited_paper_id HAVING count(DISTINCT T1.paper_id)  >  50)
answer: SELECT count(DISTINCT t1.author_id) FROM author AS t1 JOIN author_list AS t2 ON t1.author_id = t2.author_id WHERE t2.paper_id NOT IN ( SELECT paper_id FROM citation GROUP BY paper_id HAVING count(*) > 50 )

answer: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.author_id) FROM Author AS T1 INNER JOIN Author_list AS T2 ON T1.author_id = T2.author_id LEFT JOIN Paper AS T3 ON T2.paper_id = T3.paper_id WHERE T3.paper_id NOT IN ( SELECT paper_id FROM Paper )

question: What are the ids of customers who spend more than 5 on average for each good?
solution: SELECT T3.CustomerId FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.CustomerId HAVING avg(T1.price)  >  5
answer: SELECT T1.CustomerId FROM receipts AS T1 INNER JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.ReceiptNumber = T2.Receipt INNER JOIN goods AS T3 ON T2.Item = T3.Id GROUP BY T1.CustomerId, T2.Item HAVING SUM(T3.Price) / COUNT(T2.Ordinal) > 5

question: On which day did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars in total.
solution: SELECT T3.date FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.date HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  100
answer: SELECT T1.Date FROM receipts AS T1 INNER JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.ReceiptNumber = T2.Receipt INNER JOIN goods AS T3 ON T2.Item = T3.Id GROUP BY T1.ReceiptNumber HAVING SUM(T3.Price) > 100

question: On what dates did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars worth of goods in total?
solution: SELECT T3.date FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.date HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  100
answer: SELECT T1.Date FROM receipts AS T1 INNER JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.ReceiptNumber = T2.Receipt INNER JOIN goods AS T3 ON T2.Item = T3.Id GROUP BY T1.ReceiptNumber HAVING SUM(T3.Price) > 100

question: Count the number of packages sent by Ogden Wernstrom and received by Leo Wong.

question: What are the id, sic code and agency id of the client who has attended 1 meeting and has any invoice.
solution: SELECT T1.client_id ,  T1.sic_code ,  T1.agency_id FROM clients AS T1 JOIN meetings AS T2 ON T1.client_id  =  T2.client_id GROUP BY T1.client_id HAVING count(*)  =  1 INTERSECT SELECT T1.client_id ,  T1.sic_code ,  T1.agency_id FROM clients AS T1 JOIN invoices AS T2 ON T1.client_id  =  T2.client_id
answer: SELECT T1.client_id , T1.sic_code , T1.agency_id FROM Clients AS T1 JOIN Meetings AS T2 ON T1.client_id = T2.client_id JOIN Invoices AS T3 ON T1.client_id = T3.client_id GROUP BY T1.client_id HAVING COUNT(T2.meeting_id) = 1

question: Return the ids, sic codes, and agency ids of clients who have attended 1 meeting and had an invoice.

answer: SELECT T1.client_id , T1.sic_code , T1.agency_id FROM Clients AS T1 JOIN Meetings AS T2 ON T1.client_id = T2.client_id JOIN Invoices AS T3 ON T1.client_id = T3.client_id GROUP BY T1.client_id HAVING COUNT(*) = 1

question: List the start time, end time of each meeting, and the corresponding client detail and staff detail.
solution: SELECT T1.start_date_time ,  T1.end_date_time ,  T2.client_details ,  T4.staff_details FROM meetings AS T1 JOIN clients AS T2 ON T1.client_id  =  T2.client_id JOIN staff_in_meetings AS T3 ON T1.meeting_id  =  T3.meeting_id JOIN staff AS T4 ON T3.staff_id  =  T4.staff_id
answer: SELECT T1.start_date_time , T1.end_date_time , T2.client_details , T3.staff_details FROM Meetings AS T1 INNER JOIN Clients AS T2 ON T1.client_id = T2.client_id INNER JOIN Staff AS T3 INNER JOIN Staff_in_Meetings AS T4 ON T4.staff_id = T3.staff_id AND T4.meeting_id = T1.meeting_id

question: What are the start and end times of each meeting, as well as the corresponding client and staff details the attendees?
solution: SELECT T1.start_date_time ,  T1.end_date_time ,  T2.client_details ,  T4.staff_details FROM meetings AS T1 JOIN clients AS T2 ON T1.client_id  =  T2.client_id JOIN staff_in_meetings AS T3 ON T1.meeting_id  =  T3.meeting_id JOIN staff AS T4 ON T3.staff_id  =  T4.staff_id
answer: SELECT T1.start_date_time , T1.end_date_time , T2.client_details , T3.staff_details FROM Meetings AS T1 INNER JOIN Clients AS T2 ON T1.client_id = T2.client_id INNER JOIN Staff AS T3 INNER JOIN Staff_in_Meetings AS T4 ON T4.staff_id = T3.staff_id AND T4.meeting_id = T1.meeting_id
